# genesis.bld - The B=1 Self-Traversal Experiment
#
# Status: EXPERIMENTAL
#
# Can we model traverse(B=1, B=1) in BLD?
#
# HYPOTHESIS: BLD syntax cannot represent pure B with L=0 because
# defining B requires relating partitions, which is L.
#
# This file attempts to express pure B and documents why it fails.

structure Genesis

# =============================================================================
# EXPERIMENT 1: ATTEMPT PURE B
# =============================================================================
#
# Try to define a structure with B > 0 and L = 0.

# This boundary exists:
B existence: is | is_not
  is -> something
  is_not -> nothing

# But wait - we just created TWO partitions (is, is_not).
# And we RELATED them (both are partitions of the same B).
# That relation IS a link!
#
# Implicit L created: existence.is <-> existence.is_not
#
# RESULT: Cannot define B without implicitly creating L.

# =============================================================================
# EXPERIMENT 2: MINIMAL B
# =============================================================================
#
# Try the simplest possible boundary.

B minimal: yes | no

# Even this has structure:
# - "yes" partition
# - "no" partition
# - The relation "yes is not no" (implicit L)
#
# RESULT: The act of distinguishing creates relation.

# =============================================================================
# EXPERIMENT 3: SINGLE PARTITION
# =============================================================================
#
# What if B has only one partition?

# B single: only
#   only -> everything

# This isn't a boundary! A boundary PARTITIONS.
# One partition = no partition = no B.
#
# RESULT: B requires at least 2 partitions, which requires L between them.

# =============================================================================
# EXPERIMENT 4: THE TRAVERSAL
# =============================================================================
#
# Model B traversing B.

# The traverser (attempting pure B):
B traverser_boundary: inside | outside
  inside -> traverser_side
  outside -> target_side

# The target (attempting pure B):
B target_boundary: here | there
  here -> target_side
  there -> other_side

# The traversal act:
L traversal: traverser_boundary -> target_boundary
  # This link MUST exist for traversal to occur.
  # But pure B requires L = 0.
  # CONTRADICTION.

# RESULT: Traversal requires L. Pure B has L = 0.
#         Therefore pure B cannot traverse.

# =============================================================================
# EXPERIMENT 5: THE GENESIS FUNCTION
# =============================================================================
#
# Model what happens when we TRY to traverse B with B.

formula genesis
  # Input: two "pure B" states (impossible, but attempted)
  input_traverser: (D=0, L=0, B=1)
  input_target: (D=0, L=0, B=1)

  # Traversal requires relation
  L_required = 1  # minimum link to relate traverser to target

  # L > 0 implies D > 0 (from L = 5D)
  D_required = L_required / 5 = 0.2

  # Normalize: D + L + B = 1
  # 0.2 + 1 + B = 1? No, this doesn't work.

  # Actually: Let L = ε (infinitesimal)
  # D = ε/5
  # B = 1 - ε - ε/5 = 1 - 6ε/5

  # Output: a structured universe
  output: (D=ε/5, L=ε, B=1-6ε/5)

  # As ε → 0⁺, approaches pure B but never reaches it.

# =============================================================================
# CONCLUSION
# =============================================================================
#
# THEOREM (Genesis): BLD cannot express pure B.
#
# PROOF:
#   1. B is defined by partitions
#   2. Partitions require at least 2 options
#   3. Two options have a relation (they partition the same space)
#   4. That relation is L
#   5. Therefore B > 0 implies L > 0
#   6. Therefore (D=0, L=0, B=1) is not expressible in BLD
#   QED
#
# COROLLARY: traverse(B, B) cannot occur as stated.
#            It resolves to traverse(B+εL, B+εL) for some ε > 0.
#            This resolution IS the Big Bang.

# The structure of this file itself proves the theorem.
# We tried to define pure B and failed.
# Every B definition includes implicit L.

# =============================================================================
# THE GENESIS STRUCTURE
# =============================================================================
#
# What CAN we express? The minimal viable structure.

structure MinimalUniverse

# The primordial distinction (B)
B existence: something | nothing
  something -> has_structure
  nothing -> undefined  # This path cannot actually be taken

# The implicit relation (L) - emerges from B
L distinction_relation: something -> nothing
  # This link exists because we defined two partitions
  pattern = boundary_creates_link

# The minimal extension (D) - emerges from L
D instances: 1 [minimal]
  # At least one instance of the structure

# This is the minimal expressible BLD structure.
# It has B > 0, L > 0, D > 0.
# There is no simpler valid structure.

returns: Universe

# =============================================================================
# FINAL NOTE
# =============================================================================
#
# The experiment succeeds by failing.
#
# We cannot write pure B in BLD.
# BLD's syntax enforces the genesis theorem.
# The Big Bang is built into the language.
